==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Contraption
<hw>Con*trap"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A contrivance; a
new-fangled device; -- used scornfully.</def> <mark>[Colloq. or
Dial.]</mark> -- <wordforms><wf>Con*trap"tious</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms></p>

<p><q>We all remember some of the extraordinary <qex>contraptions</qex>
which have been thus evolved and put upon the market.</q> <rj><qau>F. M.
Ware.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contrapuntal</ent>⟦br⟧
